<BaseLayout title="About" description="Rustam Salavatov — solo founder, AI engineer. Building products with AI agents.">
  <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>I'm Rustam Salavatov. Solo founder, AI engineer, CTO at <a href="https://superduperai.co">SuperDuperAI</a>. Building products that help people reflect, create, and own their narrative.</p>

    <p>Started <a href="https://life2film.com">Life2Film</a> in 2014 — tools for turning everyday moments into meaningful stories. Scaled to 1M+ users. Closed in 2021. SuperDuperAI is the second chapter: AI-first products, multi-agent systems, creative tools.</p>

    <p>Father of three. Trained sail yacht captain. Based between Turkey and the US.</p>

    <h2>What I believe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Privacy is architecture, not a feature.</strong> On-device processing, local storage, no accounts when possible.</li>
      <li><strong>One pain, one feature, launch.</strong> Not platforms. Ship in days, learn from what happens.</li>
      <li><strong>Antifragile by design.</strong> Small bets with asymmetric upside. 90% safe + 10% experiments.</li>
      <li><strong>Revenue is feedback.</strong> Each product is a question to the world.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <p>AI agents do the heavy lifting — summarizing, cross-referencing, coding, testing. I steer: source ideas, direct analysis, make decisions. The repository is the agent's brain (<a href="/wiki/harness-engineering-summary">harness engineering</a>).</p>

    <p>This blog is built the same way: a <a href="/wiki">wiki</a> of synthesized knowledge, published selectively. Raw sources stay private. Compiled insights go public.</p>

    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <p>Web: Next.js + Supabase. iOS: Swift + SwiftUI. CLI: Python + uv. Performance: Rust. AI: LangChain, OpenAI, RAG, multi-agent systems. This blog: Astro + Cloudflare Pages. See all <a href="/stacks">stack templates</a>.</p>

